# Tauri App Icons

Tauri ships a default icon set (Tauri logo). Replace it by generating icons from your app image.

## Filetypes

- icon.icns = macOS
- icon.ico = Windows
- \*.png = Linux
- Square\*Logo.png & StoreLogo.png = Intended for AppX/MS Store (currently unused)

Some formats (especially PNG) may be used across platforms. Include all icons even if you build for only some platforms.

## Generate icons (pnpm)

Use a squared PNG or SVG with transparency (e.g., 1024Ã—1024).

```bash
pnpm run tauri icon ./app-icon.png
```

Arguments and options (common):

- [INPUT]: Source icon path (default: ./app-icon.png)
- -o, --output <OUTPUT>: Output directory (default: `src-tauri/icons`)
- -p, --png <PNG>: Custom PNG sizes; overrides defaults
- --ios-color <IOS_COLOR>: iOS icon background color (default: #fff)
- -v, --verbose: Verbose logging

## Where icons are placed

Desktop icons are generated to `src-tauri/icons/` by default and included automatically in builds.

To source icons from a different location, set `bundle.icon` in [src-tauri/tauri.conf.json](mdc:src-tauri/tauri.conf.json):

```json
{
  "bundle": {
    "icon": [
      "icons/32x32.png",
      "icons/128x128.png",
      "icons/128x128@2x.png",
      "icons/icon.icns",
      "icons/icon.ico"
    ]
  }
}
```

Mobile icons are written directly into the native Xcode/Android Studio projects.
